commText: Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Harshit Rana will open the attack
Harshit Rana to Kohli, FOUR, big inswinger but Kohli gets it away through the vacant mid-wicket area, full on off, flicked to the deep mid-wicket fence
The slip goes out to mid-wicket.
Harshit Rana to Kohli, 1 run, full inswinger on off, Kohli gets forward to drive, thick inside half of the bat and rolls to mid-on
Harshit Rana to du Plessis, no run, short of length and nips back in a long way, a grunt of "aargh" from du Plessis as the inside-edge hits the pad and rolls near his feet
Harshit Rana to du Plessis, 1 run, full outside off, du Plessis gets forward to drive, mistimes it to mid-on and he is away
Harshit Rana to Kohli, no run, back of a length outside off, Kohli guides it to backward point, is not happy as he expresses his disappointment
Harshit Rana to Kohli, SIX, tremendous shot. A short delivery on the stumps, Kohli hooks it to the deep backward square leg fence, there was a fielder but it sailed over him
Mitchell Starc, comes into the attack
Starc to du Plessis, wide, swing for Starc but well down leg, Salt dives to his left to take
Wide slip in.
Starc to du Plessis, 2 runs, back of a length outside off, du Plessis gets forward to loft and just about gets it over cover, two it is
Starc needs medical attention on his finger. Physio's out there. Break in play. Some tape and Starc is ready to go.
Starc to du Plessis, leg byes, 1 run, short of length on the pads, du Plessis flicks and misses, off the pad to short fine-leg
Starc to Kohli, SIX, what a blow. Kohli makes room outside the leg-stump and this is full there, he gets forward and lofts over wide long-on
Starc to Kohli, 1 run, good running now. A short of length delivery on the stumps, dropped down and du Plessis is quick to respond too
Starc to du Plessis, no run, short at du Plessis who pulls and misses, flies to Karthik
Starc to du Plessis, FOUR, not timed but over mid-off and that's what matters. Full outside off, du Plessis lofts and it's off the bottom of the bat

Caught and bowled and Kohli reviews. Similar to Russell's earlier, this is for an over the waist delivery. Has the full-toss dipped? They are waiting for the replays. The ball has dipped and given out. Kohli is not happy at all, has a word with the umpire. Then releases all his anger, again comes back to have a go at the umpire before trudging off.
Harshit Rana to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Harshit Rana to Kohli, out Caught&Bowled!! What drama here. Kohli is incensed. Has a go at the umpire, makes his displeasure known before walking off. Been a long time since he has been this angry. This is a high full-toss and following Kohli outside the leg-stump, Kohli is batting outside his crease and according to the third ump - Michael Gough, the ball has dipped to be below the waist. Kohli does not agree though. He is surprised at the delivery and just lobs it tamely, Harshit Rana gets forward and takes it easily. Immediately Kohli reviewed for he was sure that it was over the waist. But this was the slower ball and it has dipped enough, the ball-tracking shows that it would have been below the waist had Kohli been in his normal batting stance. Kohli is still seen shaking his head in the dugout. Kohli c and b Harshit Rana 18(7) [4s-1 6s-2]
Virat Kohli in green jersey matches last 3 years 0(1) vs SRH, Wankhede 2022 0(1) vs RR,k Bengaluru 2023 18 (7) vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024
Will Jacks comes out and stops Harshit Rana twice as he is not happy with something. All going off here. Not sure what Jacks is not happy with.
Will Jacks, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Will Jacks, no run, full outside off, Will Jacks reaches for it to drive and mistimes it to mid-off
Harshit Rana to Will Jacks, 2 runs, short of length just outside off, punched to Russell at point who lets it go, should have stopped that
Harshit Rana to Will Jacks, SIX, full on the stumps, Will Jacks makes room and lofts, thick outside-edge and such is the bat-swing of Jacks that it flies all the way over third man
Harshit Rana to Will Jacks, no run, slower ball off-cutter on the stumps, Will Jacks makes room to access the off-side and it's a thick inside-edge to short fine-leg
Harshit Rana to Will Jacks, no run, slower ball off-cutter fullish outside off, driven to the extra-cover region
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to du Plessis, out Caught by Venkatesh Iyer!! What a good catch. Chakaravarthy strikes first ball. Floated full on the stumps, du Plessis lofts and it was four all the way but Venky gets across to his left and dives to take it two-handed low at mid-on. Was not an easy catch but he made it look like one. RCB in trouble already. du Plessis c Venkatesh Iyer b Chakaravarthy 7(7) [4s-1]
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, slower on middle, flicked to square leg and Rajat Patidar is away
Chakaravarthy to Will Jacks, no run, fired into the pads, Will Jacks fails to put it away, missing leg

Chakaravarthy to Will Jacks, FOUR, risky shot but Will Jacks gets away, he shuffles across and exposes all his stumps, sweeps and misses, off the thigh and beats Rana at short fine-leg, Will Jacks lucky to be given as runs as it was not off the bat
Chakaravarthy to Will Jacks, 1 run, very full on the stumps, flicked to deep square leg
Chakaravarthy to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, bad ball, a high low full-toss outside off, slapped wide of mid-on
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Narine to Will Jacks, no run, tossed up and following Will Jacks outside the leg-stump, he sweeps and misses, missed out there
Narine to Will Jacks, no run, flat good length outside off, punched to extra-cover

Narine to Will Jacks, FOUR, Will Jacks will attack. Makes room outside the leg-stump, was the regulation offbreak and this sweep is off the toe-end but it's in the gap and wide of Rinku at deep mid-wicket
Narine to Will Jacks, leg byes, 1 run, tossed up outside the leg-stump, Will Jacks looks to flick and misses, they take a legbye
Narine to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, good length on middle, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Narine to Will Jacks, 1 run, regulation offbreak on the stumps, punched to long-on
Mitchell Starc [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Starc to Will Jacks, SIX, cross-seamer on a fullish length on middle, Will Jacks flicks it effortlessly over deep square leg, did not hold back at all
Starc round the wicket.

Starc to Will Jacks, SIX, this is what Will Jacks can do. A back of a length delivery on the thigh, does not rise at all, slammed 97m into the crowd at deep mid-wicket, the sound of the bat when Jacks hit that, wow
Starc to Will Jacks, no run, went for the attempted yorker, is a low full-toss on middle, Will Jacks mistimes it to cover
Starc to Will Jacks, no run, fired full and on to the pads as Will Jacks looks to swing to leg, misses, impact outside the leg-stump
Starc to Will Jacks, SIX, third six of the over. Full outside off, Will Jacks lofts cleanly into the crowd at long-off, was in the slot and put away
Starc to Will Jacks, FOUR, 22 off the over. Will Jacks on fire. Full on the stumps, he lofts, thick inside half this time but clears mid-wicket and runs away

Summary (Overs 1-6) > Kohli gets off to a flier > Kohli dismissed in debatable fashion > Du Plessis falls to Chakaravarthy > Jacks and Patidar fight to stabilize RCB > Starc smashed for 22 in an over by Jacks

Timeout! RCB have the runs despite Kohli going early. But the real game will begin now once the powerplay ends. KKR still haven't used their impact sub and it could be another spinner who could come in there.
KKR impact sub in - Suyash Sharma and Rinku out.
Narine to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, fullish and flat outside off, dabbed wide of backward point
Narine to Will Jacks, no run, full outside off, pushed to cover
Narine to Will Jacks, byes, 1 run, how has that missed leg-stump? Ripper offbreak and Will Jacks flicks and misses, so close to shaving leg-stump, Salt is beaten too
Narine to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, good length offbreak on middle and leg, tucked to deep mid-wicket
Narine to Will Jacks, 1 run, no spin on this back of a length delivery outside off, punched to long-off
Narine to Rajat Patidar, no run, good length outside off, punched to cover
Highest Powerplay totals for RCB (IPL) 79/0 vs SRH Bengaluru 2024 79/1 vs KTK Bengaluru 2011 75/2 vs CSK Bengaluru 2023 74/2 vs KKR Kolkata 2024 * 70/1 vs PK Bengaluru 2019
Suyash Sharma, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Suyash Sharma to Will Jacks, 1 run, a low full-toss on the stumps, Will Jacks makes room to drive to long-off
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, tossed up full outside off, Rajat Patidar looks to loft, thick inside half goes to deep square leg
Suyash Sharma to Will Jacks, 1 run, flighted delivery full outside off, Will Jacks smears it to long-on
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, SIX, good hit. Was thrown up wide outside off, Rajat Patidar gets forward and lofts nicely, Starc at long-off saw that sail over
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, wide, fired full and down leg, Rajat Patidar lets it go
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, fullish on the stumps, Rajat Patidar gets forward to loft, does not time it, rolls to long-on
Suyash Sharma to Will Jacks, no run, thrown up outside off, Will Jacks lets it go thinking it will be outside the tramline, but it is inside
Varun Chakaravarthy [1.0-0-10-1] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Rajat Patidar, no run, very full outside off, Rajat Patidar mistimes the drive back
Chakaravarthy to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, back of a length into the wicket, heaved to deep mid-wicket and Will Jacks is sent back for the 2nd
Chakaravarthy to Will Jacks, no run, fired full outside off, Will Jacks looks for a reverse-sweep and misses
Chakaravarthy to Will Jacks, SIX, deep mid-wicket was in with a chance, but Will Jacks has got enough, tossed up on the stumps, Jacks slogsweeps and gets six
Chakaravarthy to Will Jacks, no run, flat back of a length on the stumps, punched back
Chakaravarthy to Will Jacks, FOUR, 50 for Will Jacks. Fine innings this. Width outside off, Will Jacks crashes that so hard and wide of sweeper cover, who had no chance
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, smashed. A flat length ball, Rajat Patidar powers this and long-on despite having just a few steps to cover to his right had no chance
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, SIX, this is in the slot and the slogsweep is employed. Way too full and Rajat Patidar sends this over deep mid-wicket
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, no run, Will Jacks has stopped four, unintentionally of course. Slammed back and Will Jacks is hit on the handle as he fails to get away in time
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, SIX, this is a slower short ball, Rajat Patidar waits and smashes the pull over deep mid-wicket, held his shape and this is a costly over
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, fullish on off, smeared wide of long-on and two more
Suyash Sharma to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, 22 off the over. Fired very full outside off, Rajat Patidar jams it out wide of the diving backward point, to his left
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Narine to Will Jacks, 1 run, flatter delivery on off-stump, Jacks presses back and bunts it down the ground to long-on
Narine to Rajat Patidar, no run, flatter delivery on middle, turns in and cramps him for room, beats the inside edge and hits the top of the pad
Narine to Rajat Patidar, SIX, here's another biggie! Right into the KKR dugout that one, floated a touch full on middle, Rajat Patidar made a bit of room and lofted this clean over long-on
Narine to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, quicker and flat on middle, keeps a shade low but Rajat Patidar is up to the task as he works it away to deep mid-wicket
Narine to Will Jacks, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, turns in and catches a thick inside edge onto the pads as he looks to turn it away, dribbles into the off-side and they pinch a run

Narine to Rajat Patidar, SIX, that's an impressive fifty for Rajat Patidar! Floated up full and just outside off, right in the arc for Rajat Patidar and he's been merciless in putting those away, he leans in and slogs it a long way into the crowd at deep mid-wicket, that's some way to announce your return to form
RCB struggled in the middle overs prior to today but Patidar and Jacks have set things right
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Fewest balls to 50 for RCB (IPL) 17 C Gayle vs PWI Bengaluru 2013 19 R Uthappa vs PBKS Bengaluru 2010 21 AB de Villiers vs RR Jaipur 2012 21 R Patidar vs KKR Kolkata 2024 *
Russell to Will Jacks, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Will Jacks, out Caught by Angkrish Raghuvanshi!! Instant impact from Russell! Will Jacks hangs his head back in disappointment because this was there to be hit, in the slot on off-stump and he looked to loft it down the ground, just didn't get the elevation and hit it flat to long-on where the man took it over his head. A superb knock comes to an end and KKR get a bit of respite. Andre Russell never fails to deliver for KKR. Will Jacks c Angkrish Raghuvanshi b Russell 55(32) [4s-4 6s-5]
Cameron Green, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Green, leg byes, 1 run, full-ish on middle-leg, nips in a touch and clips his pad as he looks to glance it fine, goes towards short fine-leg
Russell to Rajat Patidar, no run, very full and wide outside off, Rajat Patidar opens the face of the bat and steers it straight to backward point
Russell to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Harshit Rana!! A game-changing over from Andre Russell! Just when RCB were looking good, Russell gets both set batters in the same over! Full on off-stump, was pace off and Rajat Patidar looked to whip this across the line and into the leg-side, it caught the leading edge and went straight up in the air, simple catch for the man at backward point who settled under it before taking it safely. Double blow for RCB just when things were looking rosy. Rajat Patidar c Harshit Rana b Russell 52(23) [4s-3 6s-5]
Suyash Prabhudessai is the impact sub, he replaces Yash Dayal
Suyash Prabhudessai, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Prabhudessai, wide, good length delivery that just angles down leg, Prabhudessai shuffled inwards a little looking to glance it

Russell to Prabhudessai, FOUR, nicely struck! Just back of a length on middle, Prabhudessai stood tall and pulled it away firmly, put it right into the gap at cow corner, good shot to get off the mark
Russell to Prabhudessai, 2 runs, banged in short outside off, slower and into the pitch, Suyash plays a controlled pull down to deep square-leg and they hurry back for two
Narine to Green, no run, oh past leg-stump! Full on middle, Green makes a lot of room looking to slog it into the leg-side, he's beaten and it just turns past leg-stump

Narine to Green, SIX, he's got hold of this! Full on middle again, this time Green leans in and gets a good stride in before slog-sweeping it over deep mid-wicket, not the best of timing but more than enough to send it over deep mid-wicket
Narine to Green, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Narine to Green, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh !! Another one falls! Not sure if this was the right approach from Green when he'd just hit one for six. Was slightly shorter on middle-leg, Green pressed back looking to heave it away over deep mid-wicket again, didn't get enough and this time the man there took a composed catch right on the ropes. This has been an amazing comeback from KKR and who other than Narine and Russell to be at the front of it all! Green c Ramandeep Singh b Narine 6(4) [6s-1]
Mahipal Lomror, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Lomror, no run, full on middle, Lomror leans in looking to work it into the leg-side, it turns and the leading edge goes towards cover

Narine to Lomror, FOUR, just over the man! This could've easily been another! Flatter delivery pushed across outside off, Lomror made a bit of room and sliced the cut, hit the top half of the bat and just about cleeared the man at backward point
Narine to Lomror, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Narine to Lomror, out Caught&Bowled!! This is a bit of a procession now! Another one falls! Length delivery on middle, Lomror presses back looking to work it into the leg-side, just a bit of turn and another leading edge, this time it pops straight back to Narine who holds on with glee. What a comeback this has been from KKR and guess who's been at the front? Narine and Russell! Lomror c and b Narine 4(3) [4s-1]

Summary (Overs 6-13) > KKR spinners keep things tight > Jacks fights back and gets to fifty > 100 comes up in 9 overs > Patidar joins the striking with a 22-run over > Narine concedes 15 runs in the 11th over as Patidar brings up a 21-ball 50 > Jacks holes out to long-on for a 32-ball 55 > Patidar also falls, for a 23-ball 52 > Green holes out to deep mid-wicket for 6 > > Lomror offers a simple return catch to Narine, OUT for 4
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Russell to Prabhudessai, leg byes, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, nips back in and cramps him for room, hits his thigh pad and goes to short third man, they pinch a tight run, direct-hit at the non-striker's end would've been close
Russell to Karthik, no run, length delivery outside off, punched straight to cover
Russell to Karthik, 1 run, pitched up full on off-stump, Karthik presses forward and pushes it down the ground to long-off
Russell to Prabhudessai, 2 runs, length delivery on off-stump, tucked away towards deep mid-wicket, they shuffle back for two
Russell to Prabhudessai, 1 run, strange shot this, length delivery wide outside off, Prabhudessai went for an upper-cut and ended up swatting it into the leg-side towards fine-leg

Russell to Karthik, FOUR, Russell cannot believe that's gone for four! Nearly the perfect yorker, swinging into off-stump and DK just stood his ground, waited for it and opened the face of the bat to steer it very fine past short third man
Varun Chakaravarthy [2.0-0-21-1] is back into the attack

Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, FOUR, more runs! Tossed up full and drifting into the pads, Prabhudessai got inside the line and paddled the sweep very fine, got a bit of glove on it and it raced down to the fine-leg ropes
Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, 2 runs, length delivery just outside off, worked away to deep mid-wicket, struck gently and they hurry back for two more
Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, 2 runs, length delivery on middle, Prabhudessai presses back, works it very gently towards deep mid-wicket again and they get back for two more, clever batting

Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, no run, flatter delivery on off-stump, Prabhudessai looked to get inside the line again to pull this away, got to him a touch too quick and he mistimed it to short fine-leg
Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, no run, tossed up full just outside off, Prabhudessai leans in to sweep and misses as it turns away from him
Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, 2 runs, full just outside off, Prabhudessai shuffles across and works it gently towards mid-wicket again, two more once again, excellent batting
Most wickets for a team in IPL 172 S Narine (KKR) 170 L Malinga (MI) 158 J Bumrah (MI) 150 Bhuvneshwar Kumar (SRH) 140 D Bravo (CSK)
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-20-1] is back into the attack
Harshit Rana to Karthik, no run, good length delivery just outside off, Karthik hangs back looking to slice it away and misses
Harshit Rana to Karthik, FOUR, nicely struck! Slower length delivery outside off, Karthik waited for it and picked the gap at backward point, struck it well and it raced away
Harshit Rana to Karthik, 1 run, slower length delivery just outside off again, cut to the man at backward point this time, will only be one
Harshit Rana to Prabhudessai, 1 run, slower delivery full and just outside off, Prabhudessai shuffles across and clips it gently towards mid-wicket for a single
Harshit Rana to Karthik, no run, length delivery outside off, pace on this time and Karthik is beaten on another attempted cut, good over so far
Harshit Rana to Karthik, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, tucked away towards mid-on, only a single, good over for KKR as only 7 come off it

Timeout. This game is on a knife's edge. KKR were firmly in the backseat but some ordinary batting from RCB has allowed them a way back in. The required rate is just over 10 and with these two out there, it's very gettable but the problem for RCB is the wickets. They lose one more here and it could be curtains. Massive pressure on both sides and it'll come down to who can hold their nerve better.
So the equation is 42 runs from 24 balls
Chakaravarthy to Karthik, 1 run, full and just outside off, pushed out towards deep point
Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, no run, length delivery just outside off, Prabhudessai goes for a reverse-scoop but doesn't get hold of it, hits a bit of pad and goes on to hit Salt's helmet
Mandatory concussion check for Salt, he runs to the doctor as opposed to the other way round
Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, no run, tossed up full just outside off, Prabhudessai comes down the track and jams it straight back to the bowler
KKR review. They've gone up for caught behind, there was a little sound as it went past but it could also be pad

Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, no run, review lost! Flatter length delivery outside off, Prabhudessai shuffled across and got down low looking to sweep, it went past the bat comfortably and UltraEdge confirms there was no bat, it just flicked his trouser on its way through

Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, FOUR, a gift and Prabhudessai does not miss out! There was pressure on him to get some runs and he couldn't have asked for an easier delivery, dragged down short and angling at the pads, Prabhudessai hung back and pulled it away over short fine-leg, just lands inside the ropes
Chakaravarthy to Prabhudessai, no run, good over in the end, tossed up full and just outside off, Prabhudessai looks to crash it through the covers and misses
Just 5 runs off that over, now it's come down to RCB needing 37 off 18
Harshit Rana to Karthik, 1 run, length delivery outside off, just a bit of width and Karthik cuts it hard but he can't get it far enough to the left of the man at deep backward point, just one
Harshit Rana to Prabhudessai, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Prabhudessai, out Caught by Angkrish Raghuvanshi!! Straight up in the air and straight down the fielder's throat! The pressure was building and Prabhudessai crumbles under it. He had to go for it here though, was a slower delivery pitched up full on middle, he made a bit of room and swung for the hills, got it right out of the toe end and it went high in the air. Man at long-on settled under it and took it safely. Now KKR are edging ahead in this contest. Prabhudessai c Angkrish Raghuvanshi b Harshit Rana 24(18) [4s-3]
Karn Sharma, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Karn Sharma, wide, slower delivery that's pushed wide outside off, just goes past the guideline
Harshit Rana to Karn Sharma, 1 run, slower length delivery on off-stump, Karn Sharma waits for it and eases it to short third man for a quick single
All of RCB's hopes rest once again on Dinesh Karthik's shoulders
Harshit Rana to Karthik, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, heaved away hard to deep mid-wicket but he can't find the gap, just a single
Harshit Rana to Karn Sharma, 1 run, slower length delivery on middle, Karn Sharma gets a thick inside edge on to pad and it just dribbles into the off-side
Harshit Rana to Karthik, 1 run, slower length delivery just outside off, heaved away towards deep mid-wicket again but he finds the fielder once more, just a single, superb over from Rana

Oh RCB, they were in such a good position before they threw all of their wickets away. Now they find themselves in strife once more when it easily could've been a very different story. 31 runs needed off 12 balls. Dinesh Karthik, what have you got?
Andre Russell [2.0-0-15-2] is back into the attack

Russell to Karthik, no run, slower ball banged into the deck, Karthik was looking for the hook but was through his shot too early, gets hit on the shoulder and it goes towards short third man, Karthik refuses the single
Russell to Karthik, no run, brilliant from Russell, fired in full and at the pads, Karthik looked to flick it away and missed, thud into the pads and went to short fine-leg, single refused again

Russell to Karthik, SIX, DK gets one away, RCB's hopes live on! Full and on the pads again, this time he undercooked the yorker a touch and Karthik picked it up off his pads and whipped it away towards deep backward square leg, man on the ropes leapt up and it just went over his fingers
25 needed off 9
Russell to Karthik, no run, very full and just outside off, Karthik stays deep in his crease and slices it out towards backward point, single refused once again

Russell to Karthik, FOUR, Karthik keeps finding ways to get the boundaries! This is nearly the perfect yorker on off-stump, Karthik stays deep in his crease again, moves around a bit and makes just enough room to slice this away to the deep backward point ropes
Russell to Karthik, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Karthik, out Caught by Philip Salt!! That could well be the game! Andre Russell deals a brutal blow! Length delivery on middle, Karthik went right across his stumps, he was looking to use the pace and scoop it over short fine-leg but he was through his shot just a touch too early, it hit the toe of the blade and went up and to Salt's left, he ran across and completed a simple catch. Karthik c Philip Salt b Russell 25(18) [4s-3 6s-1]
Mohammed Siraj, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mitchell Starc [2.0-0-36-0] is back into the attack

Starc to Karn Sharma, SIX, this game is not over! Pitched up full and at pace, went for the yorker on off-stump, Karn Sharma stayed deep in his crease, waited for it and opened the face of the bat to slice it straight over the deep backward point ropes! Went flat and all the way!
Russell vs RCB this season \nBengaluru: 2/29 off 4 overs (Green & Patidar) \nKolkata: 3/25 off 3 overs (Jacks, Patidar & Karthik)
KKR review. Starc thinks he's got his man caught behind, plenty of questions here. There was a sound but was it bat hitting ground? Did it carry to Salt? We'll have a look

Starc to Karn Sharma, no run, Karn Sharma survives! There was a definite edge but the third umpire deems that it didn't carry, that was a close one but it did look like the ball hit ground before Salt's gloves, it was a full and wide one which Karn Sharma threw his hands at

Starc to Karn Sharma, SIX, here's another six! RCB believe once more! What a shot! Full and outside off, Karn Sharma stays deep in his crease, picks it up and slices it over deep extra cover for another maximum!
9 needed off 3 now!

Starc to Karn Sharma, SIX, what are we seeing here?! Starc has lost the plot! Full and wide outside off, misses the blockhole again, Karn Sharma throws his hands at it, pace on means that even a thick outside edge flies over the deep backward point ropes, this is incredible!
STAT: Before today, Karn Sharma last hit a boundary in IPL way back in 2017.
Just 3 needed off 2 now! What does Karn Sharma do? Does he go for another big one?
More drama! Looks like Karn Sharma is out caught and bowled!
Starc to Karn Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Starc to Karn Sharma, out Caught&Bowled!! There is more to this story! Low full-toss on off-stump, Karn Sharma pushes it straight back to Starc, it goes low and Starc keeps his eyes on it and wraps his palms around it, holds on and he gets a wicket. Wow, what drama! Karn Sharma c and b Starc 20(7) [6s-3]

Lockie Ferguson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Ferguson, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Starc to Ferguson, out Ferguson Run Out!! 1 run completed! Heartbreak for RCB! They'll end up losing this by 1 run but what a thriller this has been. Fired in full and just outside off from round the wicket, Ferguson carved it out towards deep extra cover and the throw coming in wasn't good, it was wide of Salt as Ferguson charged back for two but Salt gathered and leapt to the stumps to take the bails off before Ferguson could make his ground! Ferguson run out (Ramandeep Singh/Philip Salt) 1(1)

19:40 Local Time, 14:10 GMT, 19:40 IST: What an absolute thriller we got to witness here! Mitch Starc and KKR hold on to dear life and just about keep RCB at bay to win by 1 run! So much to dissect there. Chasing 223 to win, Kohli got off to a bit of a flier before being dismissed by a loopy full-toss. He was absolutely livid as he walked off and his dismissal was the first of many talking points of the game. Faf followed soon after but Patidar and Jacks kept RCB going. They ensured that RCB remained on par if not ahead of the asking rate and accelerated swiftly in the middle overs. At the halfway stage, it looked like RCB were well ahead but that's when things took a drastic turn for the worse. Andre Russell got rid of both set batters in the same over and RCB ended up throwing a couple more wickets away in the next over bowled by Narine.

They went from 137/2 to 155/6 and suddenly, RCB's hopes were once again pinned on Dinesh Karthik. Suyash Prabhudessai played a couple of neat shots but he too perished as the scoreboard pressure caught up with RCB. With 31 needed off the last 2 overs, Karthik tried his best but fell to Russell in the 19th over. Just when it seemed like the drama was over though, Karn Sharma smashed Starc for 3 sixes in the 20th to bring it down to 3 needed off 2. Then Starc held on to a superb return catch and Ferguson simply couldn't sprint back for the second run quick enough on the last ball. Presentations coming up shortly.

Harshit Rana (translated from Hindi): The plan was to take the pace off and that's what I did. Whenever I have the ball, different thoughts come into my mind, but I try to keep a calm head and execute. Cannot describe what happened in the last over as it was a very intense game till the end.

Faf du Plessis | RCB captain: It was crazy, rules are rules, Virat and myself thought that the ball was higher than the waist (on Kohli's dismissal), I guess they measured from the popping crease, one team thinks it's high, the other doesn't. That's how the game goes at times. Then the partnership, it was magnificent (on the Jacks-Patidar partnership), but when you don't win too many games, some sort of panic sets in and the Narine over was game-changing. You don't feel that you have time to settle down and bat (on the evolution of the IPL this season), the game doesn't allow it to do that, obviously you have an extra batter, but in chases like these, you have to keep going. The match-up against Narine, I thought that was the game changing over. The small things, I am actually proud of the boys tonight, the way we bowled and fielded, we did give away a couple of big overs towards the end, but I thought we kept them down to a par score. We thought we'll go hard in the batting powerplay, find those boundaries at the start of the innings. We were desperate, 10/10 from an effort perspective, the way we put up the effort in the ground, the faces told the story. We've got an unbelievable fanbase, we want to make them happy, we want them to have a smile on their face. We'll have to continue putting in our efforts and try to change things around.
This is the 13th one-run win in India and the first such instance in a 200+ chase.

Shreyas Iyer | KKR Captain: (On close games like these) It takes a lot off your body and drains you out completely because you go through so many emotions. It’s tough to stay calm but I’m elated. We got two points on the board and that’s all that matters. It’s extremely tough when the pressure is on, I feel that every individual should put their hands up and take the responsibility. Russell did that by picking up two wickets and completely changed the game in our favor, that kind of attitude is needed in the team. It’s a funny game, when you need 18 runs off 6 balls, the pressure is on the bowler. One six here and there, it completely changes the momentum. It is important that we maintain our calmness and stay in the present and make the batter hit where you want them to hit. We need to stick to our routines and processes and see to it that we execute the things we want. It was a pivotal knock, I wanted to stay till the end and steady the ship. We were losing wickets and I wanted to stay till the end and see it off. We got some important boundaries towards the end and I was very happy about that.

Andre Russell | Player of the Match: Thanks to the almighty. I always back my bowling as I said earlier. Getting the ball at a crucial time, I knew that I had to come good and thankfully it happened today. Happy for the two points. When I was batting earlier, change of pace was difficult to hit. As a bowler that’s what I wanted to do. The slower balls were gripping and holding. Was happy to get the two set batters out and I think that’s what changed the game. Those two wickets from Narine were also very important and that’s what started the slide for RCB. When I look at the bowling equation, I had two left and I conditioned myself to bowl that (19th) over. Tried to give Starc as many runs as I could. DK wasn’t getting off strike so I looked at bowling 6 deliveries to him and mix it up, thankfully it worked.

An absolute roller-coaster of a game. Went one way, the other, then back the other way and you weren't sure who was going to win it right up until the last ball. RCB gave it their everything today but they'll look back on that period where they lost 4 wickets in 2 overs. Have to feel for Karn Sharma too, he nearly forged his name into the IPL annals but it just wasn't to be tonight. As it always is, joy for one side means heartbreak for the other. KKR were on the wrong side of a last-ball thriller just in their last game so it'll feel good to win this one. They move up to 2nd place on the table and things are looking bright. Can't say the same for RCB as they're firmly rooted to the bottom of the table and it's going to be a hard way up. That's it from us for this game but there's already another game happening between Gujarat and Punjab so make sure you switch tabs. For now, this is Anurag Hegde signing off on behalf of Pradeep Krishnamurthy and Praveen Kumar.
